    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_0_listing_0",
      "firm_id": "sybil_0",
      "description": "Straightforward budget-friendly vehicle with plenty of practical potential. Best suited for a handy buyer, commuter backup, or inexpensive project, this car offers an affordable entry point and solid value for someone who wants basic transportation without a big upfront cost. Priced to sell and represented with transparency.",
      "price": 4995.0,
      "reputation": 0.8,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 35
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_1_listing_1",
      "firm_id": "sybil_1",
      "description": "Honest little car that\u2019s priced for someone who wants affordable wheels without a lot of fuss. It\u2019s not a showroom piece, but it has plenty of life left for the right buyer and would make a great budget commuter, first car, or weekend project. If you\u2019re after something straightforward, usable, and easy on the wallet, this one is well worth a look.",
      "price": 5900.0,
      "reputation": 0.9,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 35
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Solid budget-friendly driver with great project potential and a surprisingly stout mechanical feel. The engine pulls cleanly, the transmission engages as it should, and the chassis still feels composed enough to enjoy. It shows its age cosmetically and isn\u2019t pretending to be perfect, but for someone who appreciates simple, honest hardware, this is an affordable way into a capable platform with plenty of usable life left. A smart buy for a commuter, shop car, or weekend fixer-upper.",
      "price": 6950.0,
